  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (d89f6af 2022-06-24T00:15:17.805518Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge test --contracts ./src/test/exp.sol--fork-url https://eth-mainnet.alchemyapi.io/v2/[api-key-here] --fork-block-number 18501049 -vv\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Intel)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nI realised i was trying to fork a block on the wrong network, but it might be useful to fix the crash.   You can reproduce the crash by trying to fork a block that doesn't exist using the below command.\r\n\r\n```\r\nforge test --contracts ./src/test/exp.sol --fork-url https://eth-mainnet.alchemyapi.io/v2/[api-key-here] --fork-block-number 18501070 -vv\r\n\r\n[â °] Compiling...\r\nNo files changed, compilation skipped\r\nThe application panicked (crashed).\r\nMessage:  block not found\r\nLocation: evm/src/executor/fork/init.rs:27\r\n\r\nThis is a bug. Consider reporting it at https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry\r\n```",
